## Why This Is Asked
Advanced latency management in multi-tenant clusters requires concrete CRD-driven control with observable outcomes and safe rollback.

## Key Concepts
- Kubernetes CRD and controller reconciliation loops
- Prometheus-based latency metrics (p95) and windowing
- Mitigations: HPA scaling, admission throttling, proxy-sidecar rate limits
- Status, events, auditability, and rollback semantics

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudocode: reconciliation skeleton
function reconcile(spec, status) {
  const latency = queryPrometheus(spec.namespace, spec.serviceSelector, 'p95');
  if (latency > spec.budgetMs) {
    scaleOut(spec.namespace, spec.serviceSelector);
    enableRateLimit(spec.sidecarSvc, spec.budgetMs);
  } else {
    removeRateLimit(spec.sidecarSvc);
  }
  return { observedLatency: latency, breached: latency > spec.budgetMs };
}
```

